# Events (Ивенты)

> Event = a **Publication** with `postType === 'event'`. Created via **`events.createEvent`** (not `publications.create` with that type). Calendar fields live on the publication document.

---

## Concept

- **Event post** shares the same `publications` collection as other posts but uses dedicated fields: `eventStartDate`, `eventEndDate`, optional `eventTime`, `eventLocation`, `eventAttendees` (user ids).
- **RSVP**: members of the event’s **`communityId`** (team or `isProject` community) can attend/unattend; list is `eventAttendees`.
- **Invites**: tokenized **`EventInvite`** records; **`attendViaInvite`** adds the user to `eventAttendees` **without** requiring community membership (invite-only guests).
- **Merit transfer in event context**: optional **`eventPostId`** on `meritTransfer` / `events.transferMeritInEvent` — creates a **`merit_transfer`** row and an **auto `Comment`** on the event thread (`isAutoComment: true`, `meritTransferId`). See @business-merit-transfer.mdc.

---

## Who can create events (`settings.eventCreation`)

| Mode | Who may call `events.createEvent` |
|------|-------------------------------------|
| **`admin`** (default) | Community **admin** only: `communityService.isUserAdmin` → **superadmin** or **lead** in that community. |
| **`members`** | Any user with a **role** in the community (`userCommunityRoleService.getRole` truthy) — typically **lead** or **participant**. |

Configured in **community settings** (`CommunityForm` / `communities.update`). Persisted as `settings.eventCreation`. **Future Vision** hub settings form skips this block (events are not configured there in current UI).

---

## tRPC (`events` router)

Typical procedures (see `api/apps/meriter/src/trpc/routers/events.router.ts`):

| Area | Procedures |
|------|------------|
| CRUD | `createEvent`, `updateEvent`, `deleteEvent`, `getEventsByCommunity` |
| RSVP | `attend`, `unattend`, `attendViaInvite` |
| Invites | `createInviteLink`, `getInvitePreview` (public), `inviteUser` |
| Economy | `transferMeritInEvent` (wallet + auto-comment) |

**Payment:** `createEvent` uses the same publication cost path as normal posts (quota/wallet per community `postCost` / helpers).

---

## Voting and Birzha

- **Voting** on a publication with `postType === 'event'` is **rejected** in vote creation logic (`createVoteLogic` / equivalent guard).
- **Forward / Birzha**: `proposeForward`, `forward`, and Birzha publish flows **reject** `postType === 'event'`.

Details and cross-links: @business-content.mdc.

---

## Notifications

- **`event_created`**: sent to leads + participants when an event is created (community/project name + title + date in metadata).
- **`event_invitation`**: direct invite from author/admin to a user.

`buildRedirectUrl` supports navigation to the event page from notification metadata.

---

## Web routes (canonical)

| Flow | Route |
|------|--------|
| Event page | `/meriter/event/[communityId]/[publicationId]` |
| Invite landing | `/meriter/event/invite/[token]` |
| Short invite URL (redirect) | `/event/invite/[token]` → canonical invite path |
| Events hub (community) | `/meriter/communities/[id]/events` |
| Events hub (project) | `/meriter/projects/[id]/events` |

Constants: `routes.eventView`, `routes.eventInvite`, `routes.communityEvents`, `routes.projectEvents`.

---

## Comments feed merge (auto lines)

`comments.getByPublicationId` merges **`isAutoComment`** publication-thread comments (e.g. merit-transfer log lines) **on the first page only** (`skip === 0`) ahead of vote-based rows. Full-thread sorting across pages is not merged for performance.

